{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775865656715,"sessionID":"ses_2862e79c9ffeeyo7XEFl77yktq","part":{"id":"prt_d79d77566001z34B1dMsdG60Rg","messageID":"msg_d79d742da001CSEWNSYQjyE1wW","sessionID":"ses_2862e79c9ffeeyo7XEFl77yktq","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-2042948953ec4a579ded6941290e731a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AgentCube CLI\n\nA developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install agentcube\n```\n\nOr install from source:\n\n```bash\ncd cmd/cli\npip install -e .\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nThe CLI provides commands for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking the status of AI agents.\n\n### Pack Command\n\nPackage an agent workspace by validating and preparing it:\n\n```bash\nkubectl-agentcube pack [OPTIONS]\n```\n\nOptions:\n- `-f, --workspace PATH`: Path to the agent workspace directory (default: \".\")\n- `--agent-name TEXT`: Override the agent name\n- `--language [python|java]`: Programming language\n- `--entrypoint TEXT`: Override the entrypoint command\n- `--port INTEGER`: Port to expose in the Dockerfile\n- `--build-mode [local|cloud]`: Build strategy\n- `--description TEXT`: Agent description\n- `--output PATH`: Output path for packaged workspace\n- `--verbose`: Enable detailed logging\n\nExample:\n\n```bash\nkubectl-agentcube pack --agent-name my-agent --language python --port 8080\n```\n\n### Build Command\n\nBuild a container image from the packaged agent workspace:\n\n```bash\nkubectl-agentcube build [OPTIONS]\n```\n\nOptions:\n- `-f, --workspace PATH`: Path to the agent workspace directory (default: \".\")\n- `-p, --proxy TEXT`: Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\n- `--cloud-provider TEXT`: Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\n- `--output PATH`: Output path for build artifacts\n- `--verbose`: Enable detailed logging\n\nExample:\n\n```bash\nkubectl-agentcube build --proxy http://proxy.example.com:8080\n```\n\n### Publish Command\n\nPublish an agent to the specified provider:\n\n```bash\nkubectl-agentcube publish [OPTIONS]\n```\n\nOptions:\n- `-f, --workspace PATH`: Path to the agent workspace directory (default: \".\")\n- `--version TEXT`: Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\n- `--image-url TEXT`: Image repository URL\n- `--image-username TEXT`: Username for image repository\n- `--image-password TEXT`: Password for image repository\n- `--description TEXT`: Agent description\n- `--region TEXT`: Deployment region\n- `--cloud-provider TEXT`: Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\n- `--provider [agentcube|k8s]`: Target provider (default: \"agentcube\")\n- `--node-port INTEGER`: Specific NodePort for K8s deployment\n- `--replicas INTEGER`: Number of replicas for K8s deployment\n- `--namespace TEXT`: The namespace for the deployment\n- `--verbose`: Enable detailed logging\n\nExample:\n\n```bash\nkubectl-agentcube publish --provider k8s --node-port 30080 --replicas 3\n```\n\n### Invoke Command\n\nInvoke a published agent with the given payload:\n\n```bash\nkubectl-agentcube invoke [OPTIONS]\n```\n\nOptions:\n- `-f, --workspace PATH`: Path to the agent workspace directory (default: \".\")\n- `--payload TEXT`: JSON-formatted input passed to the agent (default: \"{}\")\n- `--header TEXT`: Custom HTTP headers (can be specified multiple times)\n- `--provider [agentcube|k8s]`: Target provider (default: \"agentcube\")\n- `--verbose`: Enable detailed logging\n\nExample:\n\n```bash\nkubectl-agentcube invoke --payload '{\"message\": \"Hello\"}' --header \"Authorization: Bearer token\"\n```\n\n### Status Command\n\nGet the status of a published agent:\n\n```bash\nkubectl-agentcube status [OPTIONS]\n```\n\nOptions:\n- `-f, --workspace PATH`: Path to the agent workspace directory (default: \".\")\n- `--provider [agentcube|k8s]`: Target provider (default: \"agentcube\")\n- `--verbose`: Enable detailed logging\n\nExample:\n\n```bash\nkubectl-agentcube status --provider k8s\n```\n\n## Metadata File\n\nThe CLI uses an `agent_metadata.yaml` file to store agent configuration:\n\n```yaml\nagent_name: my-agent\ndescription: My AI agent\nlanguage: python\nentrypoint: python main.py\nport: 8080\nbuild_mode: local\nregion: us-west-1\nversion: 0.1.0\nrequirements_file: requirements.txt\n```\n\n## Development\n\n### Running Tests\n\n```bash\npytest tests/\n```\n\n### Code Quality\n\n```bash\nruff check agentcube/\nmypy agentcube/\n```\n\n## License\n\nApache-2.0","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/README.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/server/server.go\">\nERROR [50:27] undefined: store.NewValkeyStore\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_test.go\">\nERROR [138:50] cannot use mockStore (variable of type *mockStore) as store.Store value in argument to NewSandboxHandler: *mockStore does not implement store.Store (missing method GetSandboxBySessionID)\nERROR [161:36] cannot use mockStore (variable of type *mockStore) as store.Store value in argument to NewSandboxHandler: *mockStore does not implement store.Store (missing method GetSandboxBySessionID)\nERROR [181:36] cannot use mockStore (variable of type *mockStore) as store.Store value in argument to NewSandboxHandler: *mockStore does not implement store.Store (missing method GetSandboxBySessionID)\nERROR [222:50] cannot use mockStore (variable of type *mockStore) as store.Store value in argument to NewSandboxHandler: *mockStore does not implement store.Store (missing method GetSandboxBySessionID)\nERROR [247:36] cannot use mockStore (variable of type *mockStore) as store.Store value in argument to NewSandboxHandler: *mockStore does not 